      <h2>What information we collect</h2>
      <p>We may collect the following types of information:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contact details</strong> (such as name, phone number, email address).</li>
        <li><strong>Enquiry details</strong> (such as service requested, message content, location/area).</li>
        <li><strong>Communication records</strong> (messages or calls with us, including WhatsApp).</li>
        <li><strong>Basic technical data</strong> (such as device/browser information) if collected by your browser or hosting provider logs.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How we collect your information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>When you fill in an enquiry form on our website.</li>
        <li>When you contact us by phone, email, or WhatsApp.</li>
        <li>When you browse our website (basic server logs may record technical data).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How we use your information</h2>
      <p>We use your information to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Respond to enquiries and provide quotes.</li>
        <li>Arrange site visits, bookings and carry out work.</li>
        <li>Communicate about your request (calls, texts, emails, WhatsApp).</li>
        <li>Improve our services and customer experience.</li>
        <li>Keep records for accounting, tax, and business administration.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Our lawful basis for processing (UK GDPR)</h2>
      <p>We process personal data under one or more of the following lawful bases:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Consent</strong> — where you submit a form or request contact.</li>
        <li><strong>Contract</strong> — where processing is needed to provide a quote or carry out work.</li>
        <li><strong>Legitimate interests</strong> — for running our business, responding to requests, and improving services.</li>
        <li><strong>Legal obligation</strong> — for tax, accounting, or regulatory requirements.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Sharing your information</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal information. We may share your information only when necessary, for example:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>With service providers that help us operate our business (e.g., email/hosting, form processing, scheduling tools).</li>
        <li>With subcontractors or tradespeople involved in your job (only the details needed to complete the work).</li>
        <li>When required by law or to protect our legal rights.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        We keep personal information only for as long as necessary for the purposes described in this policy.
        Enquiry records may be kept for a reasonable period for customer service and business records.
        Accounting records may be kept for longer where required by law.
      </p>

      <h2>How we protect your information</h2>
      <p>
        We take reasonable measures to protect your data against loss, misuse, unauthorised access,
        alteration or disclosure. However, no website transmission can be guaranteed 100% secure.
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>Under UK data protection law, you may have rights including:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>The right to access the personal data we hold about you.</li>
        <li>The right to correct inaccurate information.</li>
        <li>The right to request deletion of your information (in certain circumstances).</li>
        <li>The right to object to processing or request restriction (in certain circumstances).</li>
        <li>The right to data portability (in certain circumstances).</li>
        <li>The right to withdraw consent where consent is the basis.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise your rights, contact us using the details above.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        Our website may use essential cookies required for basic functionality.
        If we add analytics or marketing tools in the future, we will update this policy and (where required)
        provide a cookie notice/choices.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party links</h2>
